<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="230" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[677,1210,1483,1704]" pageId="27" pageNumber="230">
DIAGNOSIS. — 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borojevic &amp; Boury-Esnault &amp; Vacelet" authorityYear="2000" box="[830,934,1554,1578]" class="Calcarea" family="Jenkinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Leucosolenida" pageId="27" pageNumber="230" phylum="Porifera" rank="family">Jenkinidae</taxonomicName>
with a simple tubular body and a sylleibid or leuconoid organization of the aquiferous system. The choanoskeleton is composed of the unpaired actine of subatrial spicules and, occasionally, the proximal part of radial diactines that cross the sponge wall.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
